the rebels see kindu as a major prize in their two-month revolt against president laurent kabila , whom they accuse of mismanagement , corruption and warmongering among congo 's 400 tribes. the rebels targeted kindu since late august , when they were forced to retreat their march from extreme western congo to the outskirts of kinshasa after angola and zimbabwe sent troops to bail out kabila. the rebels say they now control one-third of kindu , which the government has used as a staging area for a counteroffensive against rebel positions in the east. wamba said the rebels control 40